  "prompt": "What do the lyrics to \"Tunak Tunak Tun\" mean in English?",
  "response": "The song \"Tunak Tunak Tun\" by Indian singer Daler Mehndi is a high-energy bhangra track that became widely popular in the late 1990s and remains iconic today. While the song is primarily in Punjabi, it also includes nonsensical or rhythmic phrases like \"Tunak Tunak Tun\" and \"Da Da Dars.\" These phrases don\u2019t have a specific meaning but are meant to add to the song\u2019s catchy and upbeat vibe.\n\nThe actual lyrics of the song revolve around themes of love, joy, and celebration. Here\u2019s a rough translation of some lines from the song:\n\n- **\"Tunak Tunak Tun\"**: This is a rhythmic phrase without a direct meaning, used to create a lively and danceable tune.\n- **\"Nanana na nanana na\"**: Similar to the above, these are melodic fillers to enhance the song\u2019s rhythm.\n- **\"Lakh lakh vadhaiyan\"**: \"A million congratulations.\"\n- **\"Sajna ve sajna\"**: \"Beloved, oh beloved.\"\n- **\"Tere bina lagda nahi jee\"**: \"I cannot live without you.\"\n\nThe overall message of the song is one of exuberance, love, and celebration of life. The music video, which features Daler Mehndi in multiple roles, is also known for its innovative use of video effects and is considered a landmark in Indian pop culture.",
